CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 7, 1958, p. A3, reads: "Moving Day - Movers remove the cash register...last piece of equipment to go, as Loendi Club's present location becomes a nostalgic memory. President McEnheimer has a far-away look in his eyes as lone Courier salesman passes famed old residence. - All Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Loendi Club president McEnheimer watching two movers carrying cash register to moving van, with Pittsburgh Courier newspaper delivery man on sidewalk on right, in front of Loendi Club at 83 Fullerton Avenue, Hill District
